    "single_title_and_text_GYC4Nn": {
      "type": "single-title_and_text",
      "name": "Title and Text",
      "settings": {
        "title": "",
        "text": "<p>An early morning start at the florists and there they were - towering blue delphiniums. Celebrated in House & Garden’s June issue as an ‘old-fashioned’ plant to love, we couldn’t resist pairing them with the Luna tablecloth and Peony Urn runner. Their vivid blue tones looked especially striking against the soft plaster-pink walls of the Italian garden pool house, creating a table full of colour and character.</p><p>Elsewhere, the Luna Turquoise tablecloth was styled beneath a beautiful walkway draped in white wisteria. The combination of green and white, layered with moody, shade-loving planting and green Moroccan ceramics, captured the feeling of an elegant midsummer lunch in the cooling shade, offering escape from the summer heat.</p><p>Finally, just before the rain set in, the Peony Urn Pastel tablecloth was nestled amongst expertly clipped architectural hedges. Abundant peonies in matching urns became the focal point within the structured greenery. At this time of year, when so many of us are eagerly waiting for our own peonies to bloom, it was a real treat to photograph them in full, fleeting beauty - especially as Lady Calder’s garden corridor of peonies was just about to burst into flower.</p>",
        "font_type": "body",
        "vertical_alignment": "center",
        "alignment": "center",
        "color_scheme": "dark_text",
        "margin_top": "none",
        "margin_bot": "none"
      }
    },
